<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00043</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT GRANTING A FIXED MONTHLY HONORARIA AND ADDITIONAL BENEFITS TO ACCREDITED BARANGAY HEALTH WORKERS, AMENDING FOR THIS PURPOSE SECTION 6 OF REPUBLIC ACT 7883 OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE BARANGAY HEALTH WORKERS' BENEFITS AND INCENTIVES ACT OF 1995</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Provides for the fixed monthly honorarium, cash gifts, separation pay and disability benefits to all accredited Barangay Health Workers (BHWs), ensuring that the amounts provided in this measure will be adjusted to present realities based on Consumer Price Index (CPI), upon review and approval of the local health board.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>QUIMBO, ROMERO &quot;MIRO&quot; S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Gonzales (A.P.) (006 2016-08-03)</td><td>2. Zamora (M.C.) (011 2016-08-16)</td><tr><td>3. Sambar (012 2016-08-17)</td><td>4. Maceda (013 2016-08-22)</td><tr><td>5. Nieto (016 2016-08-30)</td><td>6. Espino (017 2016-08-31)</td><tr><td>7. Tan (A.) (018 2016-09-05)</td><td>8. Bravo (M.) (021 2016-09-13)</td><tr><td>9. Antonio (021 2016-09-13)</td><td>10. Dalipe (038 2016-10-18)</td><tr><td>11. Tejada (076 2017-02-28)</td><td>12. Malapitan (000 2018-03-05)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LOCAL GOVERNMENT ON 2016-07-26</td></tr></table>